history.content:
There is no estimate on the workload since this is the first time the class is offered. And you have already contacted the best resource: the professor!

However, looking at the course contents and the grading scheme, it seems to be quite challenging..

Hey guys,

I was wondering if anyone might have any guesses/insights about the workload (time commitment/difficulty of the homeworks and difficulty of concepts/exams) of CS 194-Cryptography for next semester. I emailed professor Garg about this and he directed me to the website https://people.eecs.berkeley.edu/~sanjamg/classes/cs194-spring19/ but I was not able to find information about the workload of the class. If anyone could provide me with any guesses or insights at all, I would really appreciate it since my phase 1 is very soon. Any help at all would be much appreciated!!! Thanks!!!
history.subject: Guesses about the workload of CS 194-Cryptography?
